{"id":31905,"date":"2024-02-26T07:20:00","date_gmt":"2024-02-26T01:50:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=31905"},"modified":"2024-02-26T09:51:04","modified_gmt":"2024-02-26T04:21:04","slug":"shivratri-decoration","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-decor\/shivratri-decoration\/","title":{"rendered":"Shivratri Decoration Ideas That Invite Divinity To Your Home"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Maha Shivaratri is one of the most significant festivals for Hindus across the world. It is believed that on this special occasion, the earth\u2019s northern hemisphere is positioned in a way that promotes a natural magnification of energy in humans. Thus, being awake all night with a vertically erect spine is considered to be an important ritual for Maha Shivaratri. Other rituals include fasting the whole day and bathing Lord Shiva with milk. So, to celebrate this auspicious festival, we bring to you some simple yet beautiful Shivratri decoration ideas. Elevate the positive vibrations in your home and make your space festive-ready for this spiritually powerful occasion.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some also believe that Lord Shiva married Goddess Parvati on this day, others believe that this was the day when Shiva confronted all his enemies. Many believers celebrate it as a night of stillness because Shiva became one with Mount Kailash on this very day. Whatever your belief, these Shivratri decoration ideas are sure to attract pious vibrations and elevate the spiritual quotient of your modern home.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Shivratri Decoration At Home With Flowers And Lamps<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You can never go wrong with fresh flowers and oil lamps when decorating your home for traditional festivals. Your pooja room is the centre of attraction on this day, and it deserves the royal treatment. You can also add a havan kund and some incense sticks for a lingering aroma in your entire home. Add some flower garlands and fairy lights all over your home for a soothing, festive vibe in your modern home interiors.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185342\/add-flowers-and-lamps-to-your-pooja-room-for-shivratri-decoration-at-home.jpg\" alt=\"Shivratri decoration at home add flowers and lamps to your pooja room\" class=\"wp-image-31906\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185342\/add-flowers-and-lamps-to-your-pooja-room-for-shivratri-decoration-at-home.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185342\/add-flowers-and-lamps-to-your-pooja-room-for-shivratri-decoration-at-home-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185342\/add-flowers-and-lamps-to-your-pooja-room-for-shivratri-decoration-at-home-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185342\/add-flowers-and-lamps-to-your-pooja-room-for-shivratri-decoration-at-home-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Shivratri decoration with some fresh flowers.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Shivratri Decoration Ideas For The Entryway<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This Shivratri decoration idea for your home\u2019s entryway is modern yet lends a traditional and festive mood to your home. All you need is a Maha Shivaratri-themed rangoli and a Shiva-Parvati painting on the wall. You can decorate your foyer area with some garlands, flowers and oil lamps to jazz up your home for the festival. If making a rangoli is difficult for you or you\u2019re short on time, you can opt for rangoli stickers instead.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185522\/shivratri-decoration-at-home-for-the-entryway-of-your-home.jpg\" alt=\"Shivratri decoration at home for the entryway to welcome lord shiva\" class=\"wp-image-31907\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185522\/shivratri-decoration-at-home-for-the-entryway-of-your-home.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185522\/shivratri-decoration-at-home-for-the-entryway-of-your-home-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185522\/shivratri-decoration-at-home-for-the-entryway-of-your-home-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185522\/shivratri-decoration-at-home-for-the-entryway-of-your-home-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Shivratri decoration ideas for a grand welcome to Lord Shiva<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Shiva-themed Wall Art For Your Maha Shivratri Decoration<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Maha Shivratri decoration is all about infusing the spiritual vibration into your home and yourself. So, accentuate the energy with a serene wallpaper on the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/living-room-accent-wall-designs\/\">accent wall of your living room<\/a> or adorn it with some wall art. This will help you meditate and calm your mind on this very special day and every day to come. The wall art seamlessly blends with modern modular furniture and aesthetics, adding to the style statement. Place a bowl filled with flowers and floating lamps on the coffee table to stitch the festive look together.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185715\/shivratri-decoration-ideas-with-a-shiva-themed-wallpaper-with-for-a-subtle-spiritual-touch.jpg\" alt=\"Shivratri decoration ideas go with a Shiva-themed wall art for a subtle spiritual touch\" class=\"wp-image-31908\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185715\/shivratri-decoration-ideas-with-a-shiva-themed-wallpaper-with-for-a-subtle-spiritual-touch.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185715\/shivratri-decoration-ideas-with-a-shiva-themed-wallpaper-with-for-a-subtle-spiritual-touch-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185715\/shivratri-decoration-ideas-with-a-shiva-themed-wallpaper-with-for-a-subtle-spiritual-touch-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185715\/shivratri-decoration-ideas-with-a-shiva-themed-wallpaper-with-for-a-subtle-spiritual-touch-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Shiva-themed wall art as part of Maha Shivratri decoration<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Shivratri Decoration To Give Your Balcony A Soothing Aura<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are inviting your friends at home to enjoy the festival, this Shivaratri decoration idea for the balcony is perfect for you. You can place your Shiva idol on top of your side cabinet and decorate the space with lamps, fresh flowers and incense sticks. You can use a floral backdrop to make the pooja space look more attractive. Buy it from the market or make a DIY floral backdrop using flowers and leaf torans of your choice. Place some floor cushions or low-lying seats to meditate comfortably on this auspicious day.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185921\/mahashivratri-decoration-at-home-to-give-your-balcony-a-soothing-aura.jpg\" alt=\"Mahashivratri decoration at home to give your balcony a soothing aura\" class=\"wp-image-31909\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185921\/mahashivratri-decoration-at-home-to-give-your-balcony-a-soothing-aura.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185921\/mahashivratri-decoration-at-home-to-give-your-balcony-a-soothing-aura-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185921\/mahashivratri-decoration-at-home-to-give-your-balcony-a-soothing-aura-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20185921\/mahashivratri-decoration-at-home-to-give-your-balcony-a-soothing-aura-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Create a tranquil space in your balcony with Shivratri decoration<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Minimalistic Decoration Ideas For Shivratri<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are busy managing your hectic lifestyle or do not have enough space or time to go for elaborate Shivaratri decorations at home, you can choose a sleek yet simple decor idea. Place the idol on a floating shelf and highlight the space with an attractive wallpaper. It elevates the look of your home instantly and adds definition to your walls. You can use shelves with drawers for extra storage space. You can add some lamps or candles if you please, or just keep it simple if minimalism is your way of life. This design is soothing and fits easily in your modular home setup.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20190045\/minimalistic-shivratri-decoration-ideas-for-urban-couples.jpg\" alt=\"Minimalistic shivratri decoration on a floating shelf\" class=\"wp-image-31910\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20190045\/minimalistic-shivratri-decoration-ideas-for-urban-couples.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20190045\/minimalistic-shivratri-decoration-ideas-for-urban-couples-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20190045\/minimalistic-shivratri-decoration-ideas-for-urban-couples-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/20190045\/minimalistic-shivratri-decoration-ideas-for-urban-couples-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Minimalist decoration ideas for Shivratri<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>We hope these simple Shivratri decoration ideas will help you lend a festive vibe to your home and fill your heart with joy and contentment. If you are looking for some personalised <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/\">interior design ideas<\/a> to elevate the look and functionality of your home, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/contact-us\/\">book a free consultation<\/a> now. Our designers will help you with modular and space-saving home interiors personalised as per your budget and requirements. We hope this Maha Shivaratri awakens you spiritually and helps you lead a blissful life.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Wishing you a very Happy Maha Shivaratri from the entire DesignCafe family!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you enjoyed reading about Shivaratri decoration ideas, also have a look at <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/festival-decoration-ideas\/\">festival decoration ideas<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">FAQ on Shivratri Decorations<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1. How can I decorate my home for Shivratri?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Adorn your pooja room with fresh flowers, oil lamps, havan kund, and incense sticks for a festive Shivratri decoration.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2. Are there specific colours associated with Shivratri decorations?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can use traditional colours like red, white, and saffron for a classic Shivratri decor palette.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>3. What are some creative DIY decoration ideas for Shivratri?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Create a Maha Shivaratri-themed rangoli or make rangoli stickers as a creative DIY decoration idea.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>4. Are there specific symbols or motifs associated with Shivratri decor?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can include symbols like the Shiva-Parvati painting, Shiva-themed wall art, and a serene wallpaper for a spiritual touch in Shivratri decor.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>5. Can I incorporate eco-friendly elements into Shivratri decorations?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can infuse eco-friendly elements with floral backdrops, fresh flowers, and leaf torans for a sustainable Shivratri decoration.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Functional Interior Designs?<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with smart solutions<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <